      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MATHEMATICIAN (3) scratched from Saturday to race here. Was highly impressive on debut, putting them away with plenty in hand two weeks ago. Looks a colt destined for black-type, so this shapes as the perfect stepping stone. SHOCAP (5) returns. Was well held in Listed company at Moonee Valley at her last appearance four-and-a-half months ago. Has been readied with a Pakenham trial and is one worth monitoring for any late moves. WILTSHIRE SQUARE (4) has been thereabouts since resuming and should be hitting straps now. Drops back in trip off 28 days and is worth keeping in mind. BARDIGRUB (6) was brave when getting off the mark last time on the Parks track. Needs to go up a rung or two but deserves respect. Should give backers a sight.",
